                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "After starting up Mixxx 1.10.0-beta1  in Windows 7 x64-bit, it will begin to use up a large chunk of memory, then drop it, then begin using it up again, ad so on. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "Here's an image showing my memory usage after starting it: http://imgur.com/5aOLz \n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "I do not have library scanning enabled at start-up, and my library is only 22 songs at the moment, all very small mp3's. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "My first thought was that it was memory leak that's being garbage collected, but it looks like the source code is C++, so I guess that's out the window.\n", 
